notesStmt.note: Title from title page (p. [I]); half title (p. [iii]) and spine give title Códice Perez.

msContents.summary: Manuscript facsimile of Juan Pio Perez's collection of portions of examples of the Chilam Balam, mainly consisting of calendrical and historical information, with dates in the texts ranging from 1511-2003. An appendix contains Maya legal documents, some with Spanish translations. A folder shelved with the manuscript contains 8 leaves originally laid in the manuscript, one a printed calendar table.
msContents.textLang: Maya, with Spanish notes and Spanish translations of shorter documents

supportDesc.extent: 138 leaves : 265 x 211 (179 x 136) mm. bound to 273 x 226 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, [ii], [I-III], IV-VI, 1-98, 98-99, 99, [i], 100-137, [ii], 138-174, [i], 175-180, [iv, including a foldout chart, now cracked at fold], 181-238, 240, 240-258, [x; blank]; pagination in same ink as text, Roman numerals upper center, Arabic numerals upper outer corners.

layoutDesc.layout: Text pages written in 28-29 long lines; layout varies for calendrical information in columns and calendrical diagrams.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: In the hand of C. Hermann Berendt.

binding.p: Cloth spine with marbled boards; label inside front cover reads, "Encuadernacion de Felipe Montilla, Merida de Yucatan."

origin.p: Copied in Mérida de Yucatan in 1870.

history.provenance: Copied from documents collected by Juan Pio Perez while he lived in the pueblo of Ticul.
From the collection of C. Hermann Berendt, later acquired by Daniel Garrison Brinton (ex libris stamp on title page).
